  identifying critical security vulnerabilities like forgeable admin cookies,
  various bugs in PDF generation and data handling, and lint errors. After
  realizing some lint issues were already fixed locally, the agent
  systematically addressed each problem. Key fixes included implementing a
  secure HMAC-based session management system, adding robust input validation
  and pagination to API routes, correcting sleep metric calculations in PDFs,
  and improving form field flexibility. A significant challenge arose when a
   module warning indicated potential Vercel Edge Runtime
  incompatibility for the middleware. The agent proactively refactored the
  authentication logic to use the Web Crypto API, ensuring seamless deployment
  on Vercel. All changes were committed, pushed, and verified with local builds
  and CI checks.
